summary: Scottish National Party (SNP) chief executive Peter Murrell has been charged with embezzlement amid an ongoing police investigation into the party's finances. Murrell, who is also the husband of SNP leader Nicola Sturgeon, was previously arrested in connection with the probe but released on bail. The charges against him relate to alleged embezzlement of SNP funds. Murrell has been released on bail pending a court appearance. The investigation, which involves Scotland's top law enforcement agency, the Police Scotland, is examining donations and funding arrangements within the SNP. The news has sparked a political storm in Scotland, with opposition parties calling for transparency and accountability in the investigation. Meanwhile, the SNP has expressed full cooperation with the probe and stated that it will not comment on an ongoing legal matter.

name: FA Cup
summary: The Football Association (FA) has announced significant changes to the FA Cup format for the 2024-25 season. Replays will be eliminated from the first round onwards, a move that has sparked controversy. The semi-finals and final will have new scheduling, and increased grassroots support is a key focus. The decision to scrap replays has drawn criticism from some quarters, with The Guardian describing it as "an absolute disgrace." However, the FA maintains that these changes are necessary to modernize the competition and provide a more consistent experience for fans. The calendar will also undergo alterations, with the FA Cup Final now scheduled for the same weekend as Premier League matches. This move has been criticized by some clubs, leading to a "civil war" within English football.
